<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870903-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:McDonnell Douglas Corp.</HL><DD> 09/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD </IN><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. said it plans to build a 118,000-square-foot assembly plant for its Delta rocket in Pueblo, Colo.    The St. Louis-based aerospace concern said the facility is expected to add about 250 jobs in Pueblo when it is fully operational in about two years. The company currently has a 62,000-square-foot assembly building in Pueblo and currently employs about 85 people there.    McDonnell Douglas said the new plant will be completed by March 1988 and will allow the company to meet production demand for the Delta launch vehicle. The company said it has orders and options for 28 Delta vehicles for the Air Force, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration and commercial customers.    A McDonnell Douglas spokesman couldn't be reached for comment on how much the new plant would cost. </TEXT></DOC>